* the default config file location is currently linux specific.
* if we want tongue clicks to be right click alongside a puff/blow left click, then we'll need to add logic to tongue click
to expect a LACK of energy outside the expected range.
* get blow trainer to handle both on and off events for long blows.
* debian package libportaudio2 may be all the user needs, rather than the make install thing
**** (try installing + using on a live boot)

wishlist
